  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide uppercase mb-10">
        Frequently Asked <span class="text-accent">Questions</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8" open>
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How much does a conveyor system cost?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Conveyor costs depend on seven factors: type, length/width, frame material, motor/drive, controls, environment, and installation. Gravity <a href="/conveyor-types/roller-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">roller conveyors</a> are the least expensive. Fully automated systems with servo drives and <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/sanitary/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">sanitary stainless steel</a> construction are the most expensive. Get 2&ndash;3 manufacturer quotes with a detailed specification to compare accurately.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is the most expensive part of a conveyor system?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Controls and automation typically account for 15&ndash;40% of total cost on <a href="/resources/automated-conveyor-systems/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">automated conveyor systems</a>. This includes the PLC, HMI, VFDs, servo drives, sensors, control panels, wiring, and programming. For simple conveyors, the frame and drive components dominate cost. For sanitary environments, stainless steel construction adds 50&ndash;100% over carbon steel.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            Why do conveyor prices vary so much between quotes?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Quote variation stems from scope differences — materials (carbon steel vs stainless), controls scope (motor starter vs PLC package), motor quality, design engineering time, warranty terms, and installation services. A detailed specification document ensures all vendors bid on the same scope. Use the "Questions to Ask Manufacturers" checklist above to identify scope differences between quotes.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What questions should I ask conveyor manufacturers?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Ask about controls scope (what's included vs. excluded), frame and belt materials, lead time, installation services, commissioning duration, warranty coverage (parts vs. parts + labor), wear part costs, energy consumption, and future expansion capability. See the full 18-question checklist above for the complete list.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
